{"kind":"textbox","id":"sh/p8nqxs72","slide":15,"name":"TextBox 31","text":"Quantification with DRAGEN Salmon at gene level; counts imported via tximport with a length offset into DESeq2. Two-pass filtering keeps 14,161 of 32,623 genes (85.6% mapped to SYMBOL via org.Rn.eg.db). DE model includes replicate as a batch term. Batch correction (limma) is used for visualization only — the DE tests use raw counts.","textPreview":"Quantification with DRAGEN Salmon at gene level; counts imported via tximport with a length offset into DESeq2. Two-pass filtering keeps ...","textChars":334,"textLines":1,"bbox":[86.4,494.4,1113.6,153.6]}
{"kind":"notes","id":"nt/7y1kre1w","slide":15,"text":"TIMING ~1.5 min. The pipeline in five steps. Quantification with DRAGEN Salmon at gene level; import into DESeq2 through tximport with a length offset. Two-pass filtering takes us from ~32,600 to ~14,200 genes, about 86% of which map to a gene symbol. Differential expression, GSEA, and finally an integration step where I directly compare the 5-vs-0 and 15-vs-5 contrasts. One technical but important point: I correct for batch ONLY for visualization. The statistical tests always run on raw counts with the batch term in the model — I never test on adjusted data."}
