{"kind":"textbox","id":"sh/d8v6psfi","slide":16,"name":"TextBox 10","text":"▸  Model:  ~ replicate + timepoint  (ref = Vehicle).\n▸  Replicate is the dominant variance source:\n–  PCA: replicate ≈ 52%, timepoint ≈ 34%.\n▸  Wald contrasts: 5v0, 15v0, 15v5.\n▸  LRT (reduced ~ replicate) for time-varying genes.\n▸  Significance tiers:\n–  RELAXED: padj < 0.05\n–  STRICT: padj < 0.05 & |log2FC| > 0.585 (FC > 1.5)","textPreview":"▸  Model:  ~ replicate + timepoint  (ref = Vehicle). | ▸  Replicate is the dominant variance source: | –  PCA: replicate ≈ 52%, timepoint...","textChars":329,"textLines":8,"bbox":[105.6,220.8,508.8,403.2]}
